This is how you properly eat CRAB!!! Well this is how I’ve eaten bean for my whole life. 

The body/guts is the best part of the crab. Not sure if it’s a Filipino thing but that part smacks!!!!!

Especially when you add rice and bbq to that! I use the shell as a bowl. Legit felt primal!
 
Next time you’re at a Filipino party and they serve crab, make sure you eat it this way. You won’t get disappointed!!!

NOT sponsored!!

I was randomly walking around Oakland for work and I stumbled upon @thewinkydinkydogs 

The owner Tyranny was chilling outside his restaurant and asked me if I like Hot Dogs and I was like “heck yeah”.

I told him I’m from Daly City and he said he was going to make me a “Daly City Dog”. I’m sure he was joking. 

But regardless this place was 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥

You need to eat here. Foreal. 

Tyranny, you the man!

For the next 4 days I’m only eating food that’s sold through pyramid schemes(Multi Level Marketing if you’re sensitive). 

I didn’t try all of them but I tried Herbalife, Thrive, Arbonne, and something else. Forgot the name lol. 

Btw, im not saying you can’t get healthy or lose weight on these products. Shoot, im sure iv’e lost weight because I barely ate. 

All of them tasted pretty gross except Thrive. 

Yeeeeee

Am I the only one that is getting Cooked trying to get these labubu things? Everytime they have  drop, my wife makes me go online to try to purchase them. 

So far no luck lol. Who else is getting cooked by @popmart_us @popmart

I feel like every weekend we having a family get together. I ain’t complaining!

For Father’s Day we went to my grandpas house and made some barbecue, lumpia, crab, and some other Filipino stuff. 

DM my Kuya Ryan if you want to try it!

My family is from Pampanga and we take pride on how good of a cook we are lol. I’ve been eating good my whole life! Super blessed and grateful!

Today we celebrated my nephew’s graduation in Elk Grove, so you know we eating good!

We got some Bistek, lumpia, pinakbet, and some other good stuff!!! Don’t be jelly!

If you’re looking for some good catering in Elk Grove, hit up my family @cafedubuentipo and @heavenlyfoodcreations @heavenlylumpia 

THE PANDAN SAUCE WENT CRAZY!!!

Getting Completely Cooked at Erewhon. This place is known to be the most expensive grocery store in America. We always come here on our trip to SoCal. 

I got that @garybrecka drink. This thing was $21!!! It was pretty solid. 

We also got some healthy sushi. Idk if I should even call it sushi. Then I got guacamole and chips. Dang near cost $30. Wild. 

The pad Thai was pretty solid. Probably the healthiest pad Thai I ever ate. Not sure if we can even call it pad thai.

Only eating food at Disneyland that are shaped like Mickey Mouse. 

Only ate 3 things at Disneyland / California adventure. I found out later that I should’ve gotten the Mickey shaped pretzel but I had that last time and it was whack lol. 

Literally ate nothing but sugar on our trip. But it was still fun lol.

I’m only eating food that I can get for free for the next 5 days. 

cheat code: I’m Filipino so every weekend is pretty much filled with some sort of party. 

But the other days were pretty hard. I could only eat free samples and dinner at my parents place. 

@tacobell was freakin clutch tho! Thank you to my cousin @jaacksters for letting me know that I would get a free meal if I signed up on their app lol

What should my next challenge be?

I’m only eating food from Ross for the next 3 days. 

I used to hate coming here as a kid. I still come here from time to time to buy clothes and always noticed there’s a little section food. So in this video I challenged myself to only eat food from Ross for the next 3 days. 

Do you go to Ross and do you ever buy the food?

The Pad Thai was 🔥, not going to lie lol

Celebrating Grandpa Bustos 84th birthday!!! This is some of the stuff we ate for his birthday! Ain’t nothing like a Filipino party. 

Love you gramps!!!
